<% content_for :title, "Cookie Policy" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Read Logister's cookie policy for how session, security, consent, and analytics cookies are used." %>
<% content_for :canonical_path, cookies_path %>
<% content_for :og_type, "article" %>
<% content_for :json_ld, json_ld({
  "@context" => "https://schema.org",
  "@type" => "WebPage",
  "name" => "Logister Cookie Policy",
  "url" => absolute_url_for(cookies_path),
  "description" => "Cookie policy for Logister."
}) %>

<div class="marketing-home legal-page">
  <section class="legal-hero" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-hero; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <p class="hero-kicker">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Cookie Policy</h1>
    <p class="hero-copy max-w-3xl">
      This policy explains how Logister uses cookies and similar technologies for
      authentication, security, consent management, and optional analytics.
    </p>
    <p class="legal-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2, 2026</p>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-summary-grid" style="view-transition-name: public-stats; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up">
      <p class="stat-label">Necessary cookies</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Sessions, CSRF, auth, consent state</p>
    </article>
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" data-reveal-delay-value="80">
      <p class="stat-label">Security services</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Cloudflare Turnstile where enabled</p>
    </article>
    <article class="about-pill-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" data-reveal-delay-value="140">
      <p class="stat-label">Analytics</p>
      <p class="about-pill-value">Consent-gated and deployment-configured</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="legal-card" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-workflow; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>What cookies are</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small files stored by your browser. Similar technologies, such as
        local storage and script-managed consent preferences, can also remember choices
        or support site functionality.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Strictly necessary cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Logister uses necessary cookies and similar storage so the site and application
        can work. These may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Session cookies used to keep you signed in and route requests to the correct account.</li>
        <li>CSRF and security cookies used to protect forms and authenticated actions.</li>
        <li>Remember-me cookies when you choose to stay signed in.</li>
        <li>Cookie consent preferences so we can remember your privacy choices.</li>
        <li>Security or bot-protection signals used by services such as Cloudflare Turnstile when enabled.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These cookies are required for core functionality and cannot be disabled through
        Logister's consent banner. Blocking them in your browser may prevent sign-in,
        form submission, or account features from working.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Analytics cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Logister can be configured to use Google Analytics and Cloudflare Web Analytics
        to understand aggregate product usage and site performance. These tools only load
        when analytics is enabled for the deployment and you have allowed tracking through
        the consent banner.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Third-party tools</h2>
      <p>
        Logister may use third-party scripts or services for consent management,
        analytics, and abuse prevention. These services may set or read their own cookies
        when they are enabled and allowed. Current optional services include TermsFeed
        Cookie Consent, Google Analytics, Cloudflare Web Analytics, and Cloudflare
        Turnstile.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
      <p>
        You can use the Cookie preferences link in the footer to review or change
        optional tracking choices. You can also clear or block cookies through your
        browser settings. Browser-level blocking applies to necessary cookies too, so
        some Logister features may stop working if all cookies are disabled.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy as Logister changes or as optional services are added,
        removed, or reconfigured. The updated date above shows when this page was last
        changed.
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="legal-section">
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For cookie or privacy questions, contact
        <code>support@logister.org</code>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="marketing-cta" data-controller="reveal" data-reveal-animation-class-value="reveal-up" style="view-transition-name: public-cta; view-transition-class: public-panel;">
    <div>
      <p class="workflow-kicker">Related pages</p>
      <h2>Need the broader privacy picture?</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <%= link_to "Privacy policy", privacy_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-primary" %>
      <%= link_to "Terms of use", terms_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-secondary" %>
      <%= link_to "About Logister", about_path, class: "hero-btn hero-btn-secondary" %>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
